\displaystyle \int_{0}^{\infty} J_{n}(bx) e^{-ax} \ dx \ (a,b >0, \ n=0,1,2, \ldots)
b
 \displaystyle\int_{0}^{\infty} J_{n}(bx) e^{-ax} \ dx = \displaystyle \frac{1}{2 \pi} \int_{0}^{\infty} \int_{-\pi}^{\pi}  e^{i(n \theta -bx \sin \theta)} e^{-ax} \ d \theta \ dx
 = \displaystyle \frac{1}{2 \pi} \int_{\pi}^{\pi} \int_{0}^{\infty} e^{i n \theta} e^{-(a+ib \sin \theta)x} \ dx \ d \theta
 = \displaystyle \frac{1}{2 \pi} \int_{-\pi}^{\pi} \frac{e^{i n \theta}}{a + ib \sin \theta} d \theta
z = e^{i \theta}
 = \displaystyle\frac{1}{2 \pi} \int_{|z|=1} \frac{z^{n}}{a+\frac{b}{2} \left(z-\frac{1}{z} \right)} \frac{dz} {iz} = \frac{1}{i\pi} \int_{|z|=1} \frac{z^{n}}{bz^{2}+2az-b} \ dx
\displaystyle -\frac{a}{b} \pm \frac{\sqrt{a^{2}+b^{2}}}{b}
\displaystyle -\frac{a}{b} + \frac{\sqrt{a^{2}+b^{2}}}{b}
 = \displaystyle\frac{1}{i \pi} 2 \pi i \ \text{Res} \left[ \frac{z^{n}}{bz^{2}+2az-b}, -\frac{a}{b} + \frac{\sqrt{a^{2}+b^{2}}}{b} \right]
 = b \displaystyle \ \frac{(\sqrt{a^{2}+b^{2}}-a)^{n}}{b^{n}\sqrt{a^{2}+b^{2}}}
1/b
bz^2+2az-b=b(z-z_+)(z-z_-)
z_\pm=-\frac{a}{b}\pm\frac{\sqrt{a^2+b^2}}{b}
{\rm Res}\Bigg(\frac{z^n}{b(z-z_+)(z-z_-)};\quad z=z_+\Bigg)=\lim_{z\to z_+} (z-z_+)\frac{z^n}{b(z-z_+)(z-z_-)}
